From the steps of the US Capitol to the tarmac of Kabul airport via the Olympics stadiums of Japan, AFP photographers have testified again in 2021 of a changing world. A never ending global pandemic, the violence of men and climate change, the little joys of life, the hope and the resilience of humans transpire in this collection of 120 images that were incredibly difficult to select amongst hundreds of unforgettable pictures. Enjoy.   AFP publishes a new photo album: "The Year That Changed Our World" This book recounts through 500 photos the year that changed the world, and pays tribute to solidarity and human creativity. From major capitals to Amazon villages, from Sweden to South Africa, from the richest neighborhoods to the most disadvantages places, the pandemic has affected everyone on the planet. 